{% extends "base.html.j2" %}
{% block title %}Leveling Trading{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<h1>Leveling Trading</h1>
<p>The Trading skill governs your discount when buying and your bonus when selling. It's one of nine player skills (<code>data/configs/achievements/max_level_trading.cfg</code>) and the easiest skill to level without combat.</p>

<div class="level-picker" data-skill="trading">
    <label>Your Trading level: <input type="number" min="1" max="60" value="1"></label>
    <span class="right-now">Set your level to highlight the right stage below.</span>
</div>

<h2>What to do at your level</h2>
<div class="stages">

<article class="stage" data-min="1" data-max="9"
         data-tagline="Sell smelted ingots at any outpost. Build the trade-discount perk early.">
    <div class="stage-title">Beginning <span class="level-range">level 1–9</span></div>
    <div class="stage-tagline">Convert mining surplus into qubits.</div>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Smelt before you sell.</strong> Raw ore is worth less than the ingot. Run a furnace before the first merchant trip.</li>
        <li>Visit the nearest outpost and dump everything non-essential: <a href="{{ root }}ingots.html">low-tier ingots</a>, mob drops, captured creature resources. Volume builds early XP fast.</li>
        <li>Start unlocking the <a href="#perk">Trade Discount</a> outpost perk as soon as you control an outpost. Every level shaves 2% off merchant prices.</li>
        <li>Don't worry about base_demand yet — at this stage you're selling whatever you have, not flipping.</li>
    </ul>
</article>

<article class="stage" data-min="10" data-max="19"
         data-tagline="Stack the trade-discount perk and start buying vendor-supplied parts in bulk.">
    <div class="stage-title">Mid game <span class="level-range">level 10–19</span></div>
    <div class="stage-tagline">Buy low (vendor stock), use; sell high (high-demand mob/loot items).</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Push <a href="#perk">Trade Discount</a> at your outpost. The perk applies before the skill discount, so they stack.</li>
        <li><strong>Buy vendor-supplied parts in bulk</strong> — capacitors, mirrors, wiring, even motherboards if you can afford them. Their cost at merchants is below their crafting / scavenge cost; see the bottom table.</li>
        <li>Start triaging loot: <em>keep</em> high-demand items (the top of the flip table); <em>sell</em> everything else.</li>
        <li>Avoid burning trade volume on Glowing / endgame ores yet — they fetch much more once you've levelled.</li>
    </ul>
</article>

<article class="stage" data-min="20" data-max="29"
         data-tagline="Specialise outposts by merchant type. Flip ingots → tools/weapons → qubits.">
    <div class="stage-title">Advanced <span class="level-range">level 20–29</span></div>
    <div class="stage-tagline">Multi-stop trade loops and outpost specialisation.</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Outpost specialisations affect which items have inflated demand. A mining outpost pays more for ingots; a tech outpost for electronics; a farming outpost for fruits / seeds / saplings.</li>
        <li>Plan <strong>multi-stop loops</strong>: mine on planet A → smelt → sell ingots at mining outpost → buy motherboards / parts at tech outpost → return.</li>
        <li>Quest rewards from faction merchants stack with Trading XP from the sale completion. Run faction quests that pay in items, not qubits.</li>
        <li>Start crafting tier-3 / tier-4 items <em>to flip</em>, not just use — see the high-value flip table.</li>
    </ul>
</article>

<article class="stage" data-min="30" data-max="999"
         data-tagline="Endgame trading — flip high-tier ingots and Glowing variants; max the Trade Discount perk.">
    <div class="stage-title">Endgame <span class="level-range">level 30+</span></div>
    <div class="stage-tagline">High-value flips, max perk, large volume per stop.</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Max the <a href="#perk">Trade Discount</a> perk at every outpost you hold. The compounding discount makes bulk stockpiling cheap.</li>
        <li>Flip <strong>Glowing ingots</strong> and tier-5 gem outputs through specialised merchants. The top of the high-demand table tells you where the qubits are.</li>
        <li>Hoard Motherboards bought below price and use them for the few crafts in <a href="{{ root }}guides/motherboards.html">the Motherboards guide</a> rather than reselling — vendor purchase &lt; craft value.</li>
        <li>Cash flow is no longer the bottleneck — bank everything toward MK3 ship components and Suit 4 / Scanner 4 / Jetpack 4.</li>
    </ul>
</article>

</div>

<div class="section-grid">
<div>

<h2>How XP is earned</h2>
<p>Every completed buy or sell transaction at a merchant grants Trading XP. The value of the transaction is what feeds the bar — flipping one expensive item is roughly equivalent to many cheap ones, so volume <em>or</em> value works.</p>

<h2 id="perk">The outpost perk that compounds with skill</h2>
<p>One of only three perks in <code>data/configs/outpostperks/</code> is trade-related:</p>

<table class="wiki">
<thead><tr><th>Perk</th><th class="mono">id</th><th class="numeric">Value</th><th>Effect</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td><strong>Trade Discount 1</strong></td><td class="mono">{{ trade_perk.id }}</td><td class="numeric">{{ trade_perk.value }} ({{ (trade_perk.value * 100)|round(1) }}%)</td><td>Per level, applied to merchant prices at the outpost.</td></tr>
<tr><td>HP Regen 1</td><td class="mono">{{ hp_perk.id }}</td><td class="numeric">—</td><td>Faster HP regeneration.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Processing Speed 1</td><td class="mono">{{ proc_perk.id }}</td><td class="numeric">—</td><td>Faster furnace / refinery cook times.</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<h2>What's profitable to flip — by the numbers</h2>
<p>Items in the game expose two fields the engine uses for trade pricing: <code>base_price</code> (how the merchant prices it) and <code>base_demand</code> (positive = merchant <em>wants</em> it, will pay more; negative = merchant supplies it). The most flippable items have <strong>high base price AND positive base demand</strong>:</p>

<table class="wiki">
<thead><tr><th class="icon"></th><th>Item</th><th class="numeric">Price</th><th class="numeric">Demand</th><th>Type</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for it in high_demand[:20] %}
<tr>
    <td class="icon">{% if it.icon %}<img src="{{ root }}{{ it.icon }}" alt="">{% endif %}</td>
    <td><a href="{{ root }}{{ it.url }}">{{ it.display }}</a></td>
    <td class="numeric">{{ it.base_price }}</td>
    <td class="numeric">{{ it.base_demand }}</td>
    <td class="mono">{{ it.type }}</td>
</tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="font-size:0.85em;color:var(--text-faint)">Top 20 by <code>base_demand × base_price</code>, filtered to <code>base_demand &gt; 0</code>. Sell these at the right outpost type for maximum profit.</p>

<h2>The opposite side — items merchants supply (don't flip these)</h2>
<table class="wiki">
<thead><tr><th class="icon"></th><th>Item</th><th class="numeric">Price</th><th class="numeric">Demand</th><th>Type</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for it in vendor_stock[:10] %}
<tr>
    <td class="icon">{% if it.icon %}<img src="{{ root }}{{ it.icon }}" alt="">{% endif %}</td>
    <td><a href="{{ root }}{{ it.url }}">{{ it.display }}</a></td>
    <td class="numeric">{{ it.base_price }}</td>
    <td class="numeric">{{ it.base_demand }}</td>
    <td class="mono">{{ it.type }}</td>
</tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="font-size:0.85em;color:var(--text-faint)">Lowest <code>base_demand</code>. Buy these for cheap and use them rather than flipping.</p>

</div>

<aside class="infobox">
<h3 style="margin-top:0">At a glance</h3>
<dl>
    <dt>Skill</dt><dd>Trading</dd>
    <dt>Activity</dt><dd>Buying / selling with merchants</dd>
    <dt>Stacks with</dt><dd>Trade Discount perk (2% per level)</dd>
    <dt>Where</dt><dd>Outposts, space stations, special merchants</dd>
    <dt>Achievement</dt><dd class="mono">ACH_MAX_LEVEL_TRADING</dd>
</dl>
</aside>
</div>

